terror
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:used for anything surprisingly distinctive or outstanding, either good or bad; a great one for, usu. humorous [thus different in sense or application from P8: something large or forbidding of its kind; something allegedly difficult to handle: contrast <i>Holy Terror</i> or <i>Terror</i>]


